<TITLE> Badruddoza to roll out LDP reforms by July 15 </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, July 1 (bdnews24.com)  Liberal Democratic Party (LDP) president AQM Badruddoza Chowdhury Sunday unveiled a draft reforms proposal that he said he will roll out in its final form by July 15. The proposal calls for a bar on a party member to hold a party post consecutively for three consecutive terms. He made the announcement at a seminar at a discussion meeting on political reforms at LDP headquarters at KC Memorial Clinic in Baridhara. The meeting and special prayers were held to condole the death of mother of LDP central leader Shakot Hossein Bepari. Vice-president Abdur Rashid presented the 15-point draft reform proposal. The reforms also propose if anybody from the party is elected prime minister or speaker he must give up the party post, leaders with access to the proposal said. Members will elect the party leadership at the grassroots to central level through votes. "The reform process of the party has started through this discussion. We will finalise the reform proposals in next 15 days and present it before the nation," Badroddoza said. He also proposed an increase in the seats in the parliament to 400 from 300 and more power fior the speaker. He demanded political reforms to the parliament, Election Commission and the electoral process. Party presidium member Dr MA Mannan, Joynal Abedin, Arshaduzzaman and Mahi B Chowdhury were also present. bdnews
